if we lost pem key what to do?

========================
     Recovery Options
========================

Option 1: EC2 Instance Connect (Easiest)
----------------------------------------
- Works if EC2 Instance Connect is enabled on the instance
- Go to:
  EC2 Console -> Select Instance -> Connect -> EC2 Instance Connect
- No PEM key needed (AWS handles temporary authentication)
- After login:
  Add new public key to:
  ~/.ssh/authorized_keys

echo "ssh-rsa  another" >> ~/.ssh/authorized_keys


Option 2: AWS Systems Manager (SSM) Session Manager
--------------------------------------------------
- Works if SSM Agent is installed and instance has the correct IAM role
- Go to:
  EC2 Console -> Connect -> Session Manager
- No PEM key needed
- After login:
  Add new key to:
  ~/.ssh/authorized_keys

========================================
 Option 4: Detach Root Volume & Edit
            (Last Resort)
========================================

1. Stop the instance

2. Detach the root EBS volume

3. Attach it to another EC2 instance
   where you already have access

4. Mount the volume:
   sudo mount /dev/xvdf1 /mnt

5. Edit the authorized_keys file:
   sudo nano /mnt/home/ec2-user/.ssh/authorized_keys

6. Paste your new public key

7. Detach the volume and re-attach it
   to the original instance as root
   (/dev/xvda)

8. Start the instance and connect
   using the new key
