EBS vs EFS + what happens to EBS on EC2 termination?

Key thing to remember — always set DeleteOnTermination = false for any EBS volume holding important data. Root volume deletion is the most common cause of accidental data loss on EC2.

ROOT VOLUME vs EXTRA VOLUME
─────────────────────────────
Root volume (OS disk):
  /dev/xvda or /dev/sda1
  DeleteOnTermination = TRUE by default
  EC2 dies → root EBS deleted ❌

Extra volume (data disk):
  /dev/xvdb, /dev/xvdc etc
  DeleteOnTermination = FALSE by default
  EC2 dies → extra EBS survives ✅

HOW TO CHANGE DeleteOnTermination
───────────────────────────────────
At launch time:
  EC2 Console → Launch Instance
  → Storage → Advanced
  → Delete on termination → No ✅

