for example, there is an EC2 maintenance that's been called out for after two weeks, so there is a notification has been published on the AWS dashboard for a particular EC2 instance. So now that fault has a critical change window, so you don't want that set last deadline as per the notification, but you don't want to do that. So is there a way to postpone this?

What is happening:

AWS sends notification:
"Your EC2 instance i-1234567890
requires maintenance by May 28, 2026"

You don't want maintenance on that date
Too critical for your production workload

----

Yes! You can postpone it:
--
Option 1 — Stop and Start instance:
--
This is the easiest way!

Stop instance → Start instance
        │
        ▼
AWS moves instance to new host
        │
        ▼
Maintenance automatically cleared ✅
Deadline gone ✅
No need to wait for AWS schedule
--
AWS Console:
EC2 → Instances
Select instance
Actions → Instance State → Stop
Wait for stopped
Actions → Instance State → Start
--

Why stop/start works:

Stop/Start    → moves to NEW physical host
               maintenance was for OLD host
               new host has no pending maintenance
               notification disappears ✅

Reboot        → stays on SAME host
               maintenance still pending ❌
               notification stays ❌
---
Option 2 — Reschedule from AWS Console:

Go to AWS Console
EC2 → Instances
Click your instance
        │
        ▼
Scheduled Events tab
        │
        ▼
Select the maintenance event
Click → Reschedule
Pick a new date/time
        │
        ▼
AWS reschedules to your preferred time ✅
---
Option 4 — Auto Scaling Group:

If EC2 is in ASG:
Terminate the instance
        │
        ▼
ASG launches new instance
        │
        ▼
New instance has no maintenance ✅
Old instance gone ✅
----

Types of maintenance events:

Reboot required:
→ AWS reboots your instance
→ Stop/Start clears it ✅
→ Can reschedule ✅

Retirement:
→ Hardware failing
→ Must stop/start ✅
→ Cannot avoid completely
→ Just postpone

System maintenance:
→ Network/power maintenance
→ Usually no action needed
→ AWS handles automatically
----
Summary:

Easiest fix     → Stop and Start instance
                  maintenance clears automatically

Reschedule      → pick your own date/time
                  from console or CLI

ASG instances   → terminate → new instance launched
                  no maintenance on new one

Key difference:
Stop/Start  → new host = maintenance gone ✅
Reboot      → same host = maintenance stays ❌
