When designing a VPC architecture, should a Load Balancer be placed in a public subnet or private subnet? Why?

External Load Balancer → Public Subnet:

Internet users
        │
        │ public internet
        ▼
Load Balancer (PUBLIC subnet)
        │
        │ private traffic
        ▼
Application servers (PRIVATE subnet)
        │
        │ private traffic
        ▼
Database (ISOLATED subnet)
-------------------------------
Why public subnet for external LB:

Load Balancer needs:
├── Public IP address     → to receive internet traffic
├── Internet Gateway      → to reach internet
└── Public subnet         → has route to IGW

If LB in private subnet:
→ No public IP
→ Internet cant reach it
→ Users cant access app ❌
-----

Summary:

External LB → PUBLIC subnet
→ Faces internet
→ Has public IP
→ Users access from internet
→ Routes to private app servers

Internal LB → PRIVATE subnet
→ Never faces internet
→ Only internal traffic
→ Microservices communication
→ More secure

Rule:
Anything facing internet  → public subnet
Anything internal only    → private subnet
